                 CLASSIC COOKBOOK IS REVISED

The famous cookbook "Joy of Cooking" is getting a makeover.
The most recent update was in 1977 and the Denver Post says
the venerable in-the-kitchen how-to publication is coming
out with a new edition. Famous for its bright red-and-white
checked cover -- representing a tablecloth -- the cookbook
first saw the light of day in a primitive form in the 1930s.
It was a staple in millions of households through the Great
Depression and the War Years. In 1953 it changed its focus
from being "chatty" to having a more educational text and
presentation. The new update is, according to the publica-
tion, "more visual." The content is in keeping with the
push toward leaner cuisine and for people on diets and exer-
cise programs. This latest redo was carried out under the
supervision of the grandson of the original author.


