             IMPORTED WINTERMELON ON RECALL LIST

An imported Chinese product called Wintermelon strips is on
a national government recall list. The product is packaged
in 12-ounce containers, heat-sealed in plastic. The Food
and Drug Administration recall is listed as F-103-3. The re-
call includes all products currently on the market national-
ly -- most of the distribution was in the New York area --
that were produced in the same batch. The importation was
done by Starway Inc. of Brooklyn, N.Y. The product is a com-
bination of the melon and sugar. The Wintermelon strips were
produced by the Sun Wing Hong Food Ltd. of Hong Kong. The
reason for the recall is that some amount of sulfites can
be present in the food, though no mention of that chemical
is listed on the ingredients panel.  


